In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in puree just until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in pecans and food coloring if desired. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 in. apart onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees F for 12-15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Remove to wire racks to cool.